entry.title: [autopip] Observe tabstrips more efficiently
entry.content:
Currently, the AutoPictureInPictureTabHelper uses a

BrowserTabStripTracker to observe all tabstrip changes in order to know

when to trigger autopip. This CL makes some changes to make the

tabstrip observation more efficient:



1) It only observes the tabstrip when the tab has registered for

autopip or is currently in autopip



2) While this still uses a BrowserTabStripTracker in cases where the

tabstrip is unknown (e.g. while the tab is being dragged between

tabstrips), it will observe only the current tabstrip when it is known



3) The logic has been split out into a separate helper class for easier

testing and to keep the AutoPictureInPictureTabHelper logic simpler

entry.content:

1) Create an element via `let el = document.createElement(tag);`

3) Set the text of the element via `el.textContent = '';`

4) Add the element to the do via `parentEl.appendChild(el);`



This CL adds a helper `createEl` to do 1-4 in 1 call:

`createCl(tag, parentEl, classes, text);`

entry.title: [Extensions UserScripts] Add glob support for user scripts
entry.content:
A registered user script is injected only when the URL:

- matches any "matches" pattern or any "includeGlobs" pattern, if

present

- and does not match "excludeMatches", if present

- and does not match "excludeGlobs" patterns, present.



This CL adds the "includeGlobs" and "excludeGlobs" parameters to

userScripts.register API, and hooks to the existent glob matching

functionality.



Note that the URL matching is different than the existent content

scripts. Thus, it also updates the User Scripts test to take into

account the URL matching according to their source.

entry.title: Allow Android to use RendererProcessPolicy.
entry.content:
This change sets up the sandbox to build RendererProcessPolicy and

BPFBasePolicy on Android. BPFBasePolicy now also creates a

BaselinePolicyAndroid on Android builds.



The renderer main platform delegate now checks if it's in a renderer

process and sets the RendererProcessPolicy if it is. There are no changes to the seccomp policy on other processes.



The seccomp policy itself is becoming slightly more permissive on Android as there are some syscalls allowed in RendererProcessPolicy that are currently not allowed on BaselinePolicyAndroid (setrlimit, sched_get_priority_max, sched_get_priority_min, times, uname). This change is guarded behind a feature flag so future CLs can properly clean up all the allowed syscalls, as well as determine which syscalls in AndroidBaselinePolicy can now be blocked as they're only needed by the renderer.



Bug: 739879

entry.title: view-transition: Expose viewTransition on pagereveal event
entry.content:
This CL adds a viewTransition attribute on the pagereveal event,

exposing the ViewTransition object just like the one returned from

startViewTransition in the SPA API.



A non-trivial difference in the cross-document case is that the promises

may now be accessed from multiple scripting contexts. For example, an

extension content script may add a pagereveal event handler and

access its promises. Indeed, we don't have a single entry-point from

which to set a `script_state_`, like we do with startViewTransition.



However, this isn't a problem as DOMViewTransition already uses

ScriptPromiseProperty which tracks the context of any callers and

ensures values are cloned appropriately across worlds. The only other

use for `script_state_` is for the DOMChangeFinishedCallback but the

update_dom_callback_ already tracks the state (and is accessible only in

the SPA case, so only from the context that called startViewTransition).

Thus, this CL removes `script_state_` as a member entirely.

entry.title: Vastly simplify RawPtrCountingImplWrapperForTest.
entry.content:
The motivation for this change is to allow testing of a forthcoming

AllowUninitialized trait against the RawPtrNoOpImpl regardless of what

would otherwise be selected by the combination of traits and build

flags.



By making the RawPtrCountingImplWrapperForTest always depend on the

NoOpImpl we achieve this goal. In turn, remove the word `Wrapper`

from the name as it is no longer an arbitrary wrapper but a single

Impl. Then rename the header files to match the new class name, and

rename the Trait to match as well.



By making the RawPtrCountingImplForTest a single Impl, a number of

template classes can be converted into non-template form.



By converting to non-template form, a number of sharp edges of the

C++ language are exposed.



-- Stray constexpr declarations on functions which modify state

outside of the function are now flagged as errors. The are

made non-constexpr.



-- The chromium-style rule requiring out-of-line constructors now

fires against a non-template struct. Unfortunately, this can

not be appeased by adding out-of-line constructors without also

triggering the C++20 distinction between aggregates and classes.

This distinction breaks the use of designated initializers. This

is avoided with a dummy template argument.



Since the templates are removed, the counting statistics are now

combined between dangling and non-dangling test pointer classes.

The split was likely an implementation detail arising from the use

of templates rather than a design decision, and the combined form

is simpler.

entry.content:
The reason why the button is not working is a security measure,

introduced in 2019. The idea being that the window which wants

top copy data to the clipboard is currently active. Ash will look

at the calling window and uses the |ui::EndPointType| as clipboard

source.



However, as this is triggered by a download notification from Lacros,

the currently active window is not Lacros and hence no owner can be

found, dismissing the request for copying to clipboard.



All workarounds are hacky, the usage of the button is very low and

the feature is getting reworked currently anyways. So we disable

the button for now.

entry.title: Optimize several things about DOM Parts [2/2]
entry.content:
This CL continues the optimization work, with these changes:

- Replace ClonePartsFrom() with PartRoot::CloneParts(), to centralize

the part cloning functionality into a single place.

- Replace NodeCloningData's HeapHashMap architecture with a much

simpler stack architecture. Also eliminate the cloning part queue,

and replace it with a clone-as-you-go approach. With this new

system, as a Node containing Parts is cloned, the Parts are

iterated and cloned, validating them with IsValid first. As

ChildNodeParts are encountered, they are cloned with both sibling

nodes pointing to the same node, and the new ChildNodePart is pushed

onto the part root stack. As the next_sibling is encountered, the

ChildNodePart is updated to have the correct sibling node, and the

part root stack is popped. All of this together achieves the same

behavior, but with much lower speed cost.

- Part::IsValid() is cached to improve speed, and disconnected_

becomes connected_ to avoid a `!`.

- PartRoot's cached parts list is converted from a Deque to a

HeapVector, which is more efficient. That eliminates the ability

to modify the front of the list, so this will adversely impact

performance for some operations when DOMPartsAPIActivePartTracking

is enabled (off by default).

entry.title: Fix CRD host crash in ipcz::APIObjectImpl<ipcz::Router,1>::FromObject
entry.content:
We started seeing this crash in M118 after switching to MojoIpcz. After

digging in, it appears that this problem has been around for several

years but the previous Mojo impl did not crash deterministically.



The issue is that our Daemon process creates an IpcChannelProxy server

and then attempts to launch an elevated child process. If the child

process launch fails, a method called ReportFatalError() is called

which in turn calls CloseChannel(). CloseChannel() checks whether

|channel_| has been initialized and short-circuits if so. The problem

is that a channel is open in a temp variable so cleanup isn't handled

correctly until after the temp var has been moved to |channel_|.



The fix is simple as we can just assign directly to |channel_| before

launching the child process.

entry.title: pip-pinch: Fix frozen ARC-R PiP
entry.content:
PiP for ARC-R could not be moved with touch gestures. This was caused

by the client calling `AttemptToStartDrag()` after `ET_GESTURE_BEGIN`

but before `ET_GESTURE_[SCROLL|PINCH]_BEGIN`, during which time the

`gesure_target_` was not yet set.



This regression was the result of crrev/c/4821150 which stopped using

`ET_GESTURE_BEGIN` and instead started using

`ET_GESTURE_[SCROLL|PINCH]_BEGIN` to update the `gesture_target_`. This

works fine with ARC-T but breaks PiP windows in ARC-R.



This commit introduces changes that allows `gesture_target_` to be set

immediately after `ET_GESTURE_START` so that this bug is fixed.



Bug: b/302252882

Test: Manually verified that PiP window moves with touch drag or pinch

both in ARC-R and ARC-T

entry.title: [css-masking] Support alternative properties that are aliases
entry.content:
When processing css_properties.json5, aliases go though a special

"expansion" which sets up the right enum value names, etc.

This expansion produces a list of "updated" aliases, and any existing

references to the non-updated aliases must be "manually" updated

as well. We already did this for aliases that were alternative

properties of *other* aliases (e.g.

-webkit-alternative-animation-with-timeline is an alternative of

-webkit-animation, and both are aliases), however, we neglected to

update any references held to aliases from *non-aliases*. This CL

goes through all properties and makes the necessary updates.



There is no behavior change in this CL, nor any change

to the generated code. It's a preparation to support the work

in Issue 1418401.
